cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.DS, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on stochastic service guarantee analysis of computer communication networks, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with probabilistic models for traffic and server behavior, which is related to information theory. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes time-domain models for stochastic network calculus, which can be seen as a control problem in the context of computer networks. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper presents mathematical models and proofs for the properties of stochastic network calculus, which can be viewed as algorithmic in nature. 
5. cs.PF (Performance) - The paper discusses service guarantee analysis of computer networks, which is related to performance evaluation.
